This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama during a poetry workshop with Elizabeth Alexander. The President and First Lady discuss the importance of poetry and the arts in our lives, as well as the impact it can have on individuals and society. They also highlight the work being done to bring arts education to young people and encourage the audience to pass on their knowledge and opportunities to others. The First Lady specifically praises Elizabeth Alexander for her talent and her book, "The Light of the World," which she describes as a powerful memoir about grief and healing. Overall, the article emphasizes the value and significance of poetry and the arts in our culture.